sections.title: Symptoms
content: • You try to access a member of a type (variable, method, etc.) and you get the error:
error CS0117: `________' does not contain a definition for `________'

sections.title: Cause
content: This happens when a reference is made to a member that does not exist for the data type.

error CS0117: `UnityEngine.PlayerPrefs' does not contain a definition for
`SaveGame'

sections.title: Resolution
content: Look inside the definition of a type to check if the member exists and use that member as a reference.
